description: Think of your life as the life of the fish and be sincere with yourself, if your sea stops, if your sea finds a total lack of chaos, if you don't find a way to live, how long would you endure without breathing or moving? How much agony could your mind endure? Because that is the only question that matters in life, how much do you think you are capable of agonizing over abandoning chaos in search of a false comfort? It is simply a mirage of your brain to evade the obscene idea that you die slow?
